FreeLook is an original, from-scratch implementation. It was inspired by, and
its design draws ideas from, the following open-source head tracker projects.
No source code from these projects is copied into FreeLook. They are credited
here in gratitude and for transparency about lineage.

  RC HeadTracker by Cliff Blackburn (dlktdr)
    https://github.com/dlktdr/HeadTracker
    Licensed GPL-3.0. Used only as a conceptual reference for the FrSky PARA
    wireless trainer protocol and overall feature set. No code reused.

  HeadTracker by Yury Soldak (ysoldak)
    https://github.com/ysoldak/HeadTracker
    Released into the public domain (Unlicense). Referenced for its minimalist
    automatic gyro calibration and PARA reset/compatibility approach.

The FrSky PARA (Bluetooth wireless trainer) link is a wire protocol and is
reimplemented from its observable behavior, not copied from any implementation.

Third-party components are pulled in at build time by the ESP-IDF build system
and the ESP-IDF component manager. Each such component is distributed under its
own license; see the respective component sources for details.
